- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as racetrack memory is a new technology and the paper discusses its structure and operation. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper mentions the use of multiple heads to read the data in racetrack memory. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics) is a possibility as the paper deals with the magnetic domains in racetrack memory. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category as there is no mention of neural networks or evolutionary algorithms in the paper.
